title: Mimonephelotes enganensis
text: Mimonephelotes enganensis is a species of <a href="beetle">beetle</a> in the family <a href="Cerambycidae">Cerambycidae</a>, and the only species in the genus Mimonephelotes. It was described by <a href="Stephan%20von%20Breuning%20%28entomologist%29">Breuning</a> in 1970. Breuning mistakenly thought the name was a junior homonym of the genus "Mimonephelotus" and proposed a replacement name, "Mimanhammus" in 1971, but under the <a href="ICZN">ICZN</a> the two names are not homonyms, so the original genus name is valid.
